     <h2 class="rt__h--gamma rt__h--beta">
        5. Registration for the event
    </h2>

    <p>In certain cases we allow online registration for events organised by us. Only
    mandatory information is required for a successful registration. All other
    information is voluntary.</p>
     
    <p>Mandatory fields for registration are:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>email address</li>
    <li>Name and first name</li>
    <li>Role in the event (participant*in, speaker*in, helper*in, representative*in a Wikimedia chapter)</li>
    <li>Food: vegetarians, vegans, allergies</li>
    <li>If a grant has been or is requested for the trip</li>
    <li>Has a grant been or will be applied for accommodation?</li>
    <li>Information on the name tag</li>
    <li>Adult</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Voluntary information is:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>Name of the desired room partner, if applicable</li>
    <li>Chapter through which the funding will take place</li>
    <li>Username (if already active on a Wikimedia project)</li>
    <li>First name + last name --> only if no user name is available<br>
    OR if we organize the hotel booking for the participant</li>
    <li>outward journey</li>
    <li>departure</li>
    <li>Requested rooms: SR / DR</li>
    <li>Desire for childcare</li>
    <li>Number of children</li>
    <li>Days on which the children receive care</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We use the above data to organise the participation of the person registering
    for the event and to carry out the event. The legal basis for the processing of
    this personal data is Art. 6 Para. 1 S. 1 lit. b DSGVO. We store this data for
    the above-mentioned purposes until the event is held.
    </p>

    <p>We then store the data for an additional period of three years. This storage is
    based on our legitimate interest in being able to defend ourselves against any
    legal claims that may arise from the event or to assert such claims. The legal
    basis for this is Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f DS-GMO.
    </p>

    <p>The data collected during registration will be processed internally by the
    department responsible for organising the event. In addition, the data can be
    passed on to external recipients. These include above all service providers who
    support us in the organisation and execution of the event. In addition to our
